      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QOI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly comparable to clinical hemolysis threshold; secondary QOIs (shear stress, exposure time) must be reported.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary QOI and is directly mapped to clinical threshold. Shear stress fields reported but exposure time distribution not quantified. Achieved level below required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must use the same pump geometry, blood analog, and operating envelope as the COU; any deviations must be bridged with documented extrapolation justification.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses the FDA generic pump geometry which matches the COU pump. However, blood analog viscosity differs from clinical blood at high shear, and no bridging argument provided for this deviation. Achieved level below required."
